{"id":63677,"title":"Xanthogranulomatous cholecystitis: a rare cause of digestive hemorrhage.","abstract":"Xanthogranulomatous cholecystitis is a rare affection with non-specific symptoms. It is essential to differentiate it from gall bladder adenocarcinoma. Presentation signs include hemorrhage or fistula. This report concerns a patient with pseudotumoral xanthogranulomatous cholecystitis who presented with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. ","date":"2014-02-24","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24411821","annotations":[{"name":"Cholecystitis","weight":0.906012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cholecystitis"},{"name":"Gallbladder","weight":0.831315,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallbladder"},{"name":"Adenocarcinoma","weight":0.820237,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adenocarcinoma"},{"name":"Fistula","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fistula"},{"name":"Urinary bladder","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urinary_bladder"},{"name":"Gastrointestinal bleeding","weight":0.744551,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gastrointestinal_bleeding"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.738937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Human gastrointestinal tract","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_gastrointestinal_tract"},{"name":"Digestion","weight":0.666363,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digestion"},{"name":"Bile","weight":0.579363,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bile"},{"name":"Nonspecific symptoms","weight":0.416705,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonspecific_symptoms"},{"name":"Medical sign","weight":0.311544,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_sign"}